        I_CANNOT_HELP_YOU_YOU_SHOULD_GO_FIND                                   = 7932,  -- I cannot help you. You should go find a guard from your own country.
        I_CANNOT_ACCEPT_CRYSTALS_FROM_SOMEONE_WHOSE_RANK                       = 7933,  -- I cannot accept crystals from someone whose rank is still 1. I advise you to either keep them until your reach rank 2, or to use them in craftwork.
        SINCE_WE_ARE_ALLIED_WITH_SAN_D_ORIA                                    = 7934,  -- Since we are allied with San d'Oria...
        SINCE_WE_ARE_ALLIED_WITH_BASTOK                                        = 7935,  -- Since we are allied with Bastok...
        SINCE_WE_ARE_ALLIED_WITH_WINDURST                                      = 7936,  -- Since we are allied with Windurst...
        I_AM_SORRY_I_AM_TOO_BUSY_WITH                                          = 7937,  -- I am sorry. I am too busy with other matters to be speaking with you.
        AH_YOU_HAVE_BROUGHT_US_SUPPLIES_THESE_WILL                             = 7938,  -- Ah, you have brought us supplies. These will help us indeed. I thank you.
        HMM_THESE_SUPPLIES_YOU_HAVE_BROUGHT_US_ARE                             = 7939,  -- Hmm... These supplies you have brought us are too old to be of any use. We will dispose of them promptly. I do commend you for your effort. May you succeed next time.
        YOU_VE_EARNED_CONQUEST_POINTS                                          = 7940,  -- You've earned conquest points!
        YOU_VE_RECEIVED_YOUR_NATION_S_SIGNET_YOU                               = 7941,  -- You've received your nation's Signet. You are now taking part in your nation's conquest campaign!
        I_AM_A_TEMPLE_KNIGHT_I_AM_ONE                                          = 7942,  -- I am , a Temple Knight. I am one of the guards charged with overseeing San d'Oria's conquest campaign.
        I_AM_AN_IRON_MUSKETEER_I_AM_ONE                                        = 7943,  -- I am , an Iron Musketeer. I am one of the guards charged with overseeing Bastok's conquest campaign.
        I_AM_A_WAR_WARLOCK_I_AM_ONE                                            = 7944,  -- I am , a War Warlock. I am one of the guards charged with overseeing Windurst's conquest campaign.
        WHAT_IS_YOUR_BUSINESS_WOULD_YOU_CAST_SIGNET                            = 7945,  -- What is your business? Would you cast Signet on me? I want to spend my conquest points. [I want to join the Expeditionary Force./Teleport me to the E.F. area.] I want to quit the E.F./change my E.F. I want to go on a supplies quest. I have some questions... Nothing, sorry to bother you.
        WHAT_DO_YOU_WISH_TO_KNOW_ABOUT_NOTHING                                 = 7946,  -- What do you wish to know about? Nothing. Conquests. Conquest results. Donating crystals. Conquest points. The effects of controlling regions. Regions controlled by other nations. Regions under beastman control.
        ALL_THREE_NATIONS_ARE_STRIVING_DAILY_TO_PUT                            = 7947,  -- All three nations are striving daily to put more regions under their control. This is what we call conquests. You can take part in it and serve your country by defeating enemies while you have Signet cast on you.
        EACH_REGION_COMPRISES_SEVERAL_AREAS_AND_THE_NATION                     = 7948,  -- Each region comprises several areas, and the nation that rids those areas of the most monsters gains control of the region.
        NATIONS_RECEIVE_GOODS_AND_RESOURCES_FROM_REGIONS_UNDER                 = 7949,  -- Nations receive goods and resources from regions under their control.
        SO_THE_MORE_REGIONS_WE_CONTROL_THE_RICHER                              = 7950,  -- So, the more regions we control, the richer our nation becomes.
        BORDER_GUARDS_ARE_ALSO_PLACED_IN_OUTPOSTS_WITHIN                       = 7951,  -- Border guards are also placed in outposts within regions under our control. They are there to cast Signet on adventurers like yourself.
        ONCE_YOU_HAVE_YOUR_NATION_S_SIGNET_YOU                                 = 7952,  -- Once you have your nation's Signet, you will be able to acquire crystals from enemies you defeat.
        NOT_ONLY_THAT_BUT_YOU_WILL_ALSO_RECEIVE                                = 7953,  -- Not only that, but you will also receive conquest points. You get more conquest points if you defeat enemies in regions that are not under your nation's control. These points can be used to purchase items from guards like myself.
        SO_YOU_SEE_CONQUESTS_BENEFIT_NATIONS_AND_ADVENTURERS                   = 7954,  -- So you see...conquests benefit nations and adventurers alike. We expect you to do your best to serve your country.
        YOU_CAN_SEE_THE_CURRENT_STATE_OF_CONQUESTS                             = 7955,  -- You can see the current state of conquests by selecting Region Info from the main menu. Conquest results in all regions are regularly recalculated, so you may want to check them from time to time.
        SHOPS_IN_OUR_CITY_WILL_BE_SELLING_DIFFERENT                            = 7956,  -- Shops in our city will be selling different items according to our conquest rank. The Troupe Valeriano will also visit the nation that finishes first and bring a little joy to its citizens.
        YOU_CAN_DONATE_CRYSTALS_TO_YOUR_NATION_ONCE                            = 7957,  -- You can donate crystals to your nation once you achieve rank 2. Just trade them to guards like myself, and we will ensure they are sent to the proper place.
        WE_WOULD_LIKE_YOU_TO_DONATE_CRYSTALS_TO                                = 7958,  -- We would like you to donate crystals to your nation from now on. Just trade them to guards like myself, and we will ensure they are sent to the proper place.
        YOU_CAN_ACQUIRE_CRYSTALS_BY_DEFEATING_ENEMIES_WHILE                    = 7959,  -- You can acquire crystals by defeating enemies while you have your nation's Signet. Having Signet cast on you is also the only way of taking part in conquests.
        RANK_POINTS_WILL_BE_AWARDED_TO_YOU_FOR                                 = 7960,  -- Rank points will be awarded to you for each crystal you donate, and you may be offered new missions as your rank goes up.
        YOU_ALSO_RECEIVE_RANK_POINTS_FOR_COMPLETING_MISSIONS                   = 7961,  -- You also receive rank points for completing missions. Complete missions and take part in conquests to raise your rank and serve your country.
        YOU_ARE_AWARDED_CONQUEST_POINTS_WHEN_YOU_DEFEAT                        = 7962,  -- You are awarded conquest points when you defeat monsters while you are taking part in conquests. Select "Region Info" from the menu to check your current number of conquest points.
        YOU_CAN_PURCHASE_ITEMS_FROM_GUARDS_LIKE_MYSELF                         = 7963,  -- You can purchase items from guards like myself with your conquest points, but be warned that the number of points you spend will be subtracted from your current total.
        WHEN_CONQUEST_RESULTS_ARE_ANNOUNCED_YOU_WILL_BE                        = 7964,  -- When conquest results are announced, you will be told which country controls the region you are in at that time. Sometimes regions may become neutral, or beastmen may even gain control of regions.
        IF_WE_GAIN_CONTROL_OF_A_REGION_BORDER                                  = 7965,  -- If we gain control of a region, border guards will be placed at its outposts to help adventurers like you.
        MERCHANTS_WILL_ALSO_BE_PLACED_THERE_AND_GOODS                          = 7966,  -- Merchants will also be placed there, and goods from that region will find their way to the local shops here.
        GAINING_CONTROL_OF_REGIONS_IS_THE_BASIC_PRINCIPLE                      = 7967,  -- Gaining control of regions is the basic principle behind conquests. We need each of you to do your best, and bring our nation to the top of the ranks.
        OF_COURSE_SOMETIMES_WE_LOSE_REGIONS_TO_OTHER                           = 7968,  -- Of course, sometimes we lose regions to other nations...so we must try to take them back before the next conquest results are announced.
        AS_AN_INCENTIVE_WE_WILL_AWARD_YOU_WITH                                 = 7969,  -- As an incentive, we will award you with more conquest points for defeating monsters in those regions.
        BUT_IF_WE_ARE_ALLIED_WITH_ANOTHER_NATION                               = 7970,  -- But if we are allied with another nation, you will only be awarded the regular rate for defeating monsters in our allies' regions. On the other hand, we will award you with more points for fighting in the top-ranked nation's regions.
        OUR_PARAMOUNT_CONCERN_LIES_IN_THE_BEASTMEN_GAINING                     = 7971,  -- Our paramount concern lies in the beastmen gaining control of our regions. If too many of us are defeated in a region, the beastmen will gain control of it.
        IF_THIS_HAPPENS_NOT_ONLY_IS_IT_A                                       = 7972,  -- If this happens, not only is it a great blow to our pride, but you will be unable to acquire any crystals in that region.
        THE_BEASTMEN_ARE_A_MENACE_TO_ALL_NATIONS                               = 7973,  -- The beastmen are a menace to all nations. If they rise to power, we must all unite and drive those vile creatures from that region.
        WE_NEED_YOU_TO_BRING_SUPPLIES_TO_THE                                   = 7974,  -- We need you to bring supplies to the outpost border guards who are placed in regions under our control.
        THERE_IS_ONE_OUTPOST_IN_EACH_REGION_SELECT                             = 7975,  -- There is one outpost in each region. Select Region Info from the menu, and look for the areas with a small flag mark on the map. That is where they are.
        HERE_ARE_THE_SUPPLIES_JUST_GIVE_THEM_TO                                = 7976,  -- Here are the supplies. Just give them to the guard at the outpost and your mission will be complete. Now, choose which outpost you want to go to. We give different rewards for each region, so choose carefully.
        WHERE_DO_YOU_WISH_TO_TAKE_THE_SUPPLIES                                 = 7977,  -- Where do you wish to take the supplies? @ @ @ @ @ The Ronfaure Region.[/ (Done)] The Zulkheim Region.[/ (Done)] The Norvallen Region.[/ (Done)] The Gustaberg Region.[/ (Done)] The Derfland Region.[/ (Done)] The Sarutabaruta Region.[/ (Done)] The Kolshushu Region.[/ (Done)] The Aragoneu Region.[/ (Done)] The Fauregandi Region.[/ (Done)] The Valdeaunia Region.[/ (Done)] Qufim Island.[/ (Done)] The Li'Telor Region.[/ (Done)] The Kuzotz Region.[/ (Done)] The Vollbow Region.[/ (Done)] The Elshimo Lowlands Region.[/ (Done)] The Elshimo Uplands Region.[/ (Done)] Tu'Lia.[/ (Done)] @ The Tavnazian Archipelago.[/ (Done)] @ @ @ @ @ @ @ Cancel.
        WHICH_E_F_WOULD_YOU_LIKE_TO_JOIN                                       = 7978,  -- Which E.F. would you like to join? . . . . . . The Zulkheim Region (Lv.20`). The Norvallen Region (Lv.25`). . The Derfland Region (Lv.25`). . The Kolshushu Region (Lv.20`). The Aragoneu Region (Lv.25`). The Fauregandi Region (Lv.35`). The Valdeaunia Region (Lv.40`). The Qufim Region (Lv.25`). The Li'Telor Region (Lv.35`). The Kuzotz Region (Lv.40`). The Vollbow Region (Lv.65`). The Elshimo Lowlands Region (Lv.35`). The Elshimo Uplands Region (Lv.45`). . . . . . . . . . . None.
        SO_BE_IT_YOU_HAVE_UNTIL_THE_NEXT                                       = 7979,  -- So be it. You have until the next conquest results announcement to complete this mission. Good luck.
        WE_WILL_DISPOSE_OF_THOSE_UNUSABLE_SUPPLIES                             = 7980,  -- We will dispose of those unusable supplies.
        YOU_CAN_ONLY_UNDERTAKE_ONE_SUPPLY_MISSION_PER                          = 7981,  -- You can only undertake one supply mission per day. Come back later.
        I_AM_SORRY_WE_SEEM_TO_HAVE_A                                           = 7982,  -- I am sorry. We seem to have a problem. Let me cancel it.
        YOU_DO_NOT_NEED_TO_DONATE_ANY_MORE                                     = 7983,  -- You do not need to donate any more crystals at your current rank. Speak to the guard at the gatehouse for further instructions.
        YOUR_RANK_POINTS_ARE_FULL_WE_VE_ADDED                                  = 7984,  -- Your rank points are full. We've added the excess to your conquest points. You do not need to donate any more crystals. Go to the gatehouse for further instructions.
        GOOD_WORK_CITIZEN_WE_VE_AWARDED_YOU_RANK                               = 7985,  -- Good work, citizen. We've awarded you rank points for the crystals you've donated.
        YOU_CURRENTLY_HAVE_CONQUEST_POINTS_WOULD_YOU_LIKE                      = 7986,  -- You currently have # conquest points. Would you like to use them to purchase items?
        WHICH_ITEM_DO_YOU_WISH_TO_PURCHASE_COMMON                              = 7987,  -- Which item do you wish to purchase? Common items (all ranks). 1000-pt. items (rank 1 required).000-pt. items (rank 2 required). 4000-pt. items (rank 3 required). 8000-pt. items (rank 4 required). 16000-pt. items (rank 5 required).4000-pt. items (rank 6 required).2000-pt. items (rank 7 required). 40000-pt. items (rank 8 required). 48000-pt. items (rank 9 required). 56000-pt. items (rank 10 required). Cancel.
        WHICH_ITEM_DO_YOU_WISH_TO_PURCHASE_COMMON_2                            = 7988,  -- Which item do you wish to purchase? Common items (all ranks).000-pt. items (rank 1 required). 4000-pt. items (rank 2 required). 8000-pt. items (rank 3 required). 16000-pt. items (rank 4 required).4000-pt. items (rank 5 required).2000-pt. items (rank 6 required). 40000-pt. items (rank 7 required). 48000-pt. items (rank 8 required). 56000-pt. items (rank 9 required). . Cancel.
        CURRENTLY_THERE_ARE_NO_ITEMS_AVAILABLE_FOR_THAT                        = 7989,  -- Currently there are no items available for that rank.
        DUE_TO_ITS_SPECIAL_NATURE_YOU_CAN_ONLY                                 = 7990,  -- Due to its special nature, you can only purchase or recharge % once until the conquest results tally is performed. Also, you cannot purchase this item if a similar item is already in your possession.
        IT_IS_POSSIBLE_TO_FULLY_RECHARGE_BY_TRADING                            = 7991,  -- It is possible to fully recharge % by trading it to one of your nation's guards, including outpost guards. One charge requires 50 conquest points.
        IT_IS_POSSIBLE_TO_FULLY_RECHARGE_BY_TRADING_2                          = 7992,  -- It is possible to fully recharge % by trading it to one of your nation's guards, including outpost guards. One charge requires 100 conquest points.
        IT_IS_POSSIBLE_TO_FULLY_RECHARGE_BY_TRADING_3                          = 7993,  -- It is possible to fully recharge % by trading it to one of your nation's guards, including outpost guards. One charge requires 200 conquest points.
        DURING_THE_TIME_OF_THE_GREAT_WAR_IT                                    = 7994,  -- During the time of the Great War, it was possible to have this item recharged in exchange for Allied Notes. From my understanding, that practice has recently become commonplace in the Near East. Though you'll be needing Imperial Standing credits if you wish to use the service there.
        YOU_DO_NOT_POSSESS_THE_REQUIRED_TO_FULLY                               = 7995,  -- You do not possess the # [conquest point/conquest points] required to fully recharge the %.
        PLEASE_BE_AWARE_THAT_YOU_CAN_ONLY_PURCHASE                             = 7996,  -- Please be aware that you can only purchase or recharge % once during the period between each conquest results tally.
        THE_IS_ALREADY_FULLY_CHARGED                                           = 7997,  -- The % is already fully charged.
        YOUR_HAS_RECEIVED_IN_EXCHANGE_FOR_IT_IS                                = 7998,  -- Your % has received # [charge/charges] in exchange for # [conquest point/conquest points]. It is now fully recharged.
        I_WILL_TRADE_YOU_FOR_YOUR_MAY_IT                                       = 7999,  -- I will trade you % for your %. May it serve you well.
        YOU_DO_NOT_MEET_THE_REQUIREMENTS_TO_PURCHASE                           = 8000,  -- You do not meet the requirements to purchase the %.
        YOUR_RANK_IS_TOO_LOW_TO_PURCHASE_THE                                   = 8001,  -- Your rank is too low to purchase the %.
        YOU_DO_NOT_HAVE_ENOUGH_CONQUEST_POINTS_TO                              = 8002,  -- You do not have enough conquest points to purchase the %.
        YOU_CANNOT_EQUIP_THE_DO_YOU_STILL_WISH                                 = 8003,  -- You cannot equip the %. Do you still wish to proceed?
        YOUR_LEVEL_IS_TOO_LOW_TO_EQUIP_THE                                     = 8004,  -- Your level is too low to equip the %. Do you still wish to proceed?
        YOU_SEEM_TO_BE_ABLE_TO_EQUIP_THE                                       = 8005,  -- You seem to be able to equip the %. Do you wish to proceed?
        ARE_YOU_SURE_YOU_WANT_TO_PURCHASE_THE                                  = 8006,  -- Are you sure you want to purchase the %?
        PROCEED_YES_PURCHASE_ITEM_CANCEL_PURCHASE                              = 8007,  -- Proceed? Yes, purchase item. Cancel purchase.
        PROCEED_YES_EVEN_THOUGH_I_CAN_T_EQUIP                                  = 8008,  -- Proceed? Yes, even though I can't equip it. Cancel purchase.
        WHICH_ITEM_DO_YOU_WISH_TO_PURCHASE_NEXT                                = 8009,  -- Which item do you wish to purchase? %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. Next page. Previous page. Back.
        WHICH_ITEM_DO_YOU_WISH_TO_PURCHASE_PTS                                 = 8010,  -- Which item do you wish to purchase? %...# pts. %...# pts. %...# pts. %...# pts. %...# pts. %...# pts. %...# pts. %...# pts. Next page. Previous page. Back.
        ENDPARAF                                                               = 8011,  -- ENDPARAF#
        WHICH_SERVICE_DO_YOU_REQUEST_BUY_SELL_ITEMS                            = 8012,  -- Which service do you request? Buy/Sell items. Teleportation. Nothing.
        DO_YOU_REALLY_WISH_TO_BE_TELEPORTED_YES                                = 8013,  -- Do you really wish to be teleported? Yes. Teleport with gil. Teleport with conquest points. No.
        WELCOME_TO_THE_BORDER_SHOP_IF_YOU_TRADE                                = 8014,  -- Welcome to the border shop! If you trade me unused equipment, I'll add their value to your country's region points!
        IT_SHOULD_PLEASE_YOU_TO_KNOW_THAT_I                                    = 8015,  -- It should please you to know that I now also deal in %. Bigger pieces will earn you more points for your nation, and I'll even toss some gil into the equation!
        I_SEE_THAT_YOUR_HOME_COUNTRY_HAS_CONTROL                               = 8016,  -- I see that your home country has control of this region. Feel free to browse through my wares.
        I_SEE_THAT_YOUR_HOME_COUNTRY_IS_ALLIES                                 = 8017,  -- I see that your home country is allies with the country in control of this region. Feel free to browse through my wares.
        I_CAN_TELEPORT_YOU_TO_YOUR_HOME_COUNTRY                                = 8018,  -- I can teleport you to your home country for # gil or # conquest [point/points].
        WORD_HAS_IT_THAT_THE_ENTIRE_SET_OF                                     = 8019,  -- Word has it that the entire set of mog tablets has been recovered. Oh, happy day! In honor of the occasion, I can teleport you to your home country free of charge.
        I_AM_TERRIBLY_SORRY_BUT_IT_SEEMS_AS                                    = 8020,  -- I am terribly sorry, but it seems as if you do not have enough gil.
        I_AM_TERRIBLY_SORRY_BUT_IT_SEEMS_AS_2                                  = 8021,  -- I am terribly sorry, but it seems as if you do not have enough conquest points.
        HOWEVER_DUE_TO_YOUR_HOME_COUNTRY_S_LACK                                = 8022,  -- However, due to your home country's lack of influence in the region, this is the only transaction I am authorized to perform with you at the moment.
        I_AM_LOOKING_FORWARD_TO_DOING_BUSINESS_WITH                            = 8023,  -- I am looking forward to doing business with you again in the future!
        THANK_YOU_THIS_WILL_INCREASE_YOUR_NATION_S                             = 8024,  -- Thank you. This will increase your nation's region points by a small amount. If you have anything else, by all means, trade them to me.
        THANK_YOU_THIS_WILL_INCREASE_YOUR_NATION_S_2                           = 8025,  -- Thank you. This will increase your nation's region points moderately. If you have anything else, by all means, trade them to me.
        THANK_YOU_THIS_WILL_INCREASE_YOUR_NATION_S_3                           = 8026,  -- Thank you. This will increase your nation's region points greatly. If you have anything else, by all means, trade them to me.
        I_COULD_NOT_ACCEPT_ONE_OR_MORE_ITEMS                                   = 8027,  -- I could not accept one or more items you tried to trade me. Please remove those items and try again.
        SORRY_I_CAN_ONLY_TAKE_CERTAIN_TYPES_OF                                 = 8028,  -- Sorry. I can only take certain types of weapons, shields, or armor.
        THANK_YOU_THIS_WILL_INCREASE_YOUR_NATION_S_4                           = 8029,  -- Thank you. This will increase your nation's region points [by a small amount/moderately/greatly]. For this transaction I will also furnish you with # gil.
        MY_APOLOGIES_BUT_THIS_TYPE_OF_ITEM_NEEDS                               = 8030,  -- My apologies, but this type of item needs to be individually appraised. Please trade them to me one at a time.
        DEBUG_BACK_TO_HOMETOWN                                                 = 8031,  -- (DEBUG) Back to hometown!
        WHAT_DO_YOU_WANT_WOULD_YOU_CAST_SIGNET                                 = 8032,  -- What do you want? Would you cast Signet on me? I'd like to set my home point here. Nothing.
        WHAT_DO_YOU_WANT_PAY_GIL_AND_SET                                       = 8033,  -- What do you want? Pay # gil and set my home point here. Nothing.
        YOUR_HOME_POINT_HAS_BEEN_SET                                           = 8034,  -- Your home point has been set.
        YOU_DO_NOT_HAVE_ENOUGH_GIL_TO_SET                                      = 8035,  -- You do not have enough gil to set your home point here.
        I_WILL_SET_YOUR_HOME_POINT_HERE                                        = 8036,  -- I will set your home point here.
        WE_ARE_CURRENTLY_ON_A_BEASTMAN_PURGING_CAMPAIGN                        = 8037,  -- We are currently on a beastman-purging campaign. We support adventurers from all nations. Do your best to rid the world of those vile creatures.
        WE_ARE_CURRENTLY_CONDUCTING_AN_INTERNATIONAL_EXCHANGE_CAMPAIGN         = 8038,  -- We are currently conducting an international exchange campaign. You may spend your conquest points to purchase items from foreign guards.
        THANKS_TO_YOU_OUR_NATION_IS_NOW_FIRST                                  = 8039,  -- Thanks to you, our nation is now first in the conquest race! Here is a small token of our appreciation.
        ADVENTURERS_FROM_NATIONS_THAT_ARE_RANKED_HIGHER_THAN                   = 8040,  -- Adventurers from nations that are ranked higher than ours in the conquest race may purchase items from us, but at a higher rate.
        YOU_CANNOT_CURRENTLY_PURCHASE_THIS_ITEM_PLEASE_CHOOSE                  = 8041,  -- You cannot currently purchase this item. Please choose another.
        CURRENTLY_OUR_NATION_IS_DISPATCHING_EXPEDITIONARY_FORCES_ACROSS        = 8042,  -- Currently our nation is dispatching Expeditionary Forces across Vana'diel, and requests the participation of brave adventurers such as yourself.
        REQUIREMENTS_FOR_PARTICIPATING_IN_AN_E_F_ARE                           = 8043,  -- Requirements for participating in an E.F. are simple. Your party must consist of # members. Each member must be from this country, rank 3 or higher, and have reached a sufficient level.
        ONCE_YOUR_PARTY_IS_READY_COME_TO_ME                                    = 8044,  -- Once your party is ready, come to me and I will teleport you to the nearest outpost.
        THERE_YOU_WILL_RECEIVE_AN_INSIGNIA_OF_THE                              = 8045,  -- There, you will receive an insignia of the Expeditionary Force. When you succeed in taking control of the area, you can exchange the insignia for your reward.
        JOIN_THE_E_F_IN_JOIN_THE_E                                             = 8046,  -- Join the E.F. in [Ronfaure/Zulkheim/Norvallen/Gustaberg/Derfland/Sarutabaruta/Kolshushu/Aragoneu/Fauregandi/Valdeaunia/Qufim/Li'Telor/Kuzotz/Vollbow/The Elshimo Lowlands/The Elshimo Uplands]? Join the E.F. Not this time.
        YOUR_PARTY_DOESN_T_HAVE_ENOUGH_MEMBERS_OR                              = 8047,  -- Your party doesn't have enough members, or some of the members are not in this area. Gather all those who are participating and return here.
        ONE_OF_YOUR_PARTY_MEMBERS_IS_NOT_A                                     = 8048,  -- One of your party members is not a citizen of this country. We do not allow any foreign participants in the E.F.
        ONE_OF_YOUR_PARTY_MEMBERS_HAS_NOT_ACHIEVED                             = 8049,  -- One of your party members has not achieved rank level 3. We cannot reveal any of our tactical strategies to those who have not shown their loyalty to our country.
        ONE_OF_YOUR_PARTY_MEMBERS_IS_BELOW_LEVEL                               = 8050,  -- One of your party members is below level #. For the safety of the adventurer and those accompanying him or her, we cannot allow anyone below the limit to participate in the E.F.
        I_SEE_THAT_YOU_ARE_READY_I_GRANT                                       = 8051,  -- I see that you are ready. I grant you permission to join the current Expeditionary Force. When you are ready to teleport to the outpost, talk to me once more.
        ARE_YOU_READY_TO_BE_TELEPORTED_TO_REMEMBER                             = 8052,  -- Are you ready to be teleported to [Ronfaure/Zulkheim/Norvallen/Gustaberg/Derfland/Sarutabaruta/Kolshushu/Aragoneu/Fauregandi/Valdeaunia/Qufim/Li'Telor/Kuzotz/Vollbow/The Elshimo Lowlands/The Elshimo Uplands]? Remember that party members who have not been granted permission to attend the E.F. will be left behind.
        TELEPORT_TO_READY_WAIT_JUST_A_MINUTE                                   = 8053,  -- Teleport to [Ronfaure/Zulkheim/Norvallen/Gustaberg/Derfland/Sarutabaruta/Kolshushu/Aragoneu/Fauregandi/Valdeaunia/Qufim/Li'Telor/Kuzotz/Vollbow/The Elshimo Lowlands/The Elshimo Uplands]? Ready! Wait just a minute...
        CANCEL_YOUR_PARTICIPATION_IN_THE_E_F_TO                                = 8054,  -- Cancel your participation in the E.F. to [Ronfaure/Zulkheim/Norvallen/Gustaberg/Derfland/Sarutabaruta/Kolshushu/Aragoneu/Fauregandi/Valdeaunia/Qufim/Li'Telor/Kuzotz/Vollbow/The Elshimo Lowlands/The Elshimo Uplands]?
        QUIT_THE_E_F_YES_CHANGE_LOCATIONS_NO                                   = 8055,  -- Quit the E.F.? Yes. Change locations. No.
        ARE_YOU_SURE                                                           = 8056,  -- Are you sure?
        REALLY_QUIT_THE_E_F_YES_NO                                             = 8057,  -- Really quit the E.F.? Yes. No.
        I_SEE_IF_YOU_EVER_WISH_TO_PARTICIPATE                                  = 8058,  -- I see. If you ever wish to participate in the future, I will be waiting here to take your application.
        YOUR_EF_BADGE_VANISHES                                                 = 8059,  -- Your EF Badge vanishes!
        KATSU_YAKU_POINTOS                                                     = 8060,  -- Katsu-yaku pointos : #!
        THIS_IS_NO_LONGER_VALID_WE_WILL_DISPOSE                                = 8061,  -- This % is no longer valid. We will dispose of it here.
        YOUR_INVALID_ENSIGNIAS_HAVE_BEEN_DISPOSED_OF                           = 8062,  -- Your invalid ensignias have been disposed of.
        WELCOME_BACK_FROM_THE_EXPEDITION_OUR_NATION_WAS                        = 8063,  -- Welcome back from the expedition. Our nation was successful in its campaign. Let me give you your reward.
        YOU_RECEIVED_CONQUEST_POINTS                                           = 8064,  -- You received # conquest points!
        WHEN_PARTICIPATING_IN_AN_EXPEDITIONARY_FORCE_CONCENTRATE_YOUR          = 8065,  -- When participating in an Expeditionary Force, concentrate your efforts on fighting foes that give you the most experience points. And don't forget to confiscate the contents of any beastman treasure chest you happen to come upon.
        I_WILL_NOW_HAND_YOU_YOUR_INSIGNIA_BE                                   = 8066,  -- I will now hand you your insignia. Be sure to read the inscription on the back before you begin your duties. Once Signet has been bestowed upon you, prepare to be teleported.
        YOU_COULD_NOT_BE_TELEPORTED_ASK_ME_AGAIN                               = 8067,  -- You could not be teleported. Ask me again, please.
        THE_CONQUEST_RESULTS_ARE_CURRENTLY_BEING_TALLIED_COME                  = 8068,  -- The conquest results are currently being tallied. Come back later.
        YOU_HAVE_RECEIVED_PERMISSION_TO_JOIN_THE_EXPEDITIONARY                 = 8069,  -- You have received permission to join the Expeditionary Forces!
        CURRENTLY_WE_RANK_FIRST_IN_VANA_DIEL_S                                 = 8070,  -- Currently we rank first in Vana'diel's conquest, but that must not be taken for granted. We must continue our fight to remain on top.
        WE_HAD_FIRST_PLACE_IN_OUR_HANDS_BUT                                    = 8071,  -- We had first place in our hands, but we let it slip away. If we want to be ranked first in Vana'diel, each and every one of us must do their part. I look forward to hearing of your achievements.
        OUR_COUNTRY_HAS_FALLEN_TO_THIRD_IN_THE                                 = 8072,  -- Our country has fallen to third in the conquest of Vana'diel. We must step up our efforts to improve the situation.
        YOU_MUST_FIGHT_IN_BATTLES_THAT_GAIN_HIGH                               = 8073,  -- You must fight in battles that gain high levels of experience. This is the only way we can bring areas under our country's control.
        CURRENTLY_OUR_COUNTRY_IS_THE_DOMINANT_FORCE_IN                         = 8074,  -- Currently, our country is the dominant force in this region. If we can maintain this level, control of this area will be ours.
        CURRENTLY_OUR_COUNTRY_IS_A_MAJOR_FORCE_IN                              = 8075,  -- Currently, our country is a major force in this region. However, we cannot take this for granted. If we let down our guard, we will surely lose control of the area!
        CURRENTLY_OUR_COUNTRY_HAS_ONLY_MINOR_INFLUENCE_IN                      = 8076,  -- Currently, our country has only minor influence in this region. We're counting on you to get us out of this hole we've dug ourselves into.
        CURRENTLY_OUR_COUNTRY_S_INFLUENCE_IN_THIS_AREA                         = 8077,  -- Currently, our country's influence in this area is minimal. If we do not act quickly, control of this region will certainly be taken by a rival country.
        TAKE_CARE_WHEN_PASSING_THROUGH_AS_THIS_AREA                            = 8078,  -- Take care when passing through, as this area is currently overrun with beastmen! Something must be done, or the enemy will have control of the entire region.
        YOUR_INVENTORY_IS_FULL_YOU_COULD_NOT_ACCEPT                            = 8079,  -- Your inventory is full. You could not accept the %.
        YOU_ALREADY_POSSESS_A_GATE_GLYPH_YOU_CANNOT                            = 8080,  -- You already possess a gate glyph. You cannot hold any more.
        I_AM_JEUNOAN_DUCAL_GUARD_MY_DUTY_IS                                    = 8081,  -- I am Jeunoan Ducal Guard, . My duty is to support the conquest efforts of Windurst, San d'Oria, and Bastok.
        PAUSE                                                                  = 8271,  -- PAUSE
        NEIGH_NEIGH_AH_IT_S_THE_YEAR_OF                                        = 8273,  -- Neigh! Neigh! (Ah, it's the Year of the Horse.)
        NEEEIGH_NEEEIGH_NEEEIGH_AH_IT_S_THE_YEAR                               = 8274,  -- Neeeigh! Neeeigh! Neeeigh!!! (Ah, it's the Year of the Horse.)
        NEEEEEEIGH_NEIGH_NEEEEIGH_NEW_YEAR_S_GREETING_HE                       = 8275,  -- Neeeeeeigh! Neigh! Neeeeigh!!! (New Year's greeting? He looks very happy!)
        NEEEEEEIGH_NEEEIGH_NEEEIGH_YOU_WILL_BE_BLESSED_WITH                    = 8276,  -- Neeeeeeigh! Neeeigh! Neeeigh!!! (You will be blessed with unlimited happiness.)
        NEEEIGH_NEEEIGH_YOUR_YEAR_WILL_BE_OVERFLOWING_WITH                     = 8277,  -- Neeeigh! Neeeigh!! (Your year will be overflowing with joy.)
        NEIGH_NEEEIGH_YOUR_YEAR_WILL_BE_FILLED_WITH                            = 8278,  -- Neigh! Neeeigh!! (Your year will be filled with peace and love.)
        NEIGH_YOUR_YEAR_WILL_BE_AS_JOYFUL_AS                                   = 8279,  -- Neigh!! (Your year will be as joyful as the last.)
        NEIGH_YOUR_YEAR_WILL_BE_FAIRLY_GOOD                                    = 8280,  -- Neigh! (Your year will be fairly good...)
        NEIGH_NEIGH_YOUR_YEAR_WILL_BRING_FLEAS_LOTS                            = 8281,  -- Neigh... Neigh... (Your year will bring fleas...lots of fleas.)
        THE_LIGHT_I_CAN_FEEL_ITS_POWER_RUN                                     = 8282,  -- The [orange/1/2/3/red/red/blue/blue/yellow/yellow/green/green/indigo/indigo/violet/violet] light... I can feel its power run through me.
        COME_FOLLOW_ME                                                         = 8283,  -- Come, %. Follow me...
        CARBUNCLE_VANISHED_OFF_IN_THE_DIRECTION_OF_THE                         = 8284,  -- Carbuncle vanished off in the direction of the La Theine Plateau.
        CARBUNCLE_VANISHED_OFF_TO_ANOTHER_AREA_IN_THE                          = 8285,  -- Carbuncle vanished off to another area in the La Theine Plateau.
        THE_JUMPS_IN_YOUR_HANDS                                                = 8286,  -- The % jumps in your hands.
        AHAHAHAHAHA_I_CAN_SENSE_THE_POWER_OF_THE                               = 8287,  -- Ahahahahaha! I can sense the power of the ring! Get yourself moving [north/northeast/east/southeast/south/southwest/west/northwest]!
        AHAHAHAHAHA_DON_T_SLOW_DOWN_NOW_SLACKER_THE                            = 8288,  -- Ahahahahaha! Don't slow down now, slacker! The readings are coming from the [north/northeast/east/southeast/south/southwest/west/northwest]!
        AHAHAHAHAHA_YOU_RE_GETTING_CLOSE_NOW_I_CAN                             = 8289,  -- Ahahahahaha! You're getting close now! I can feel the ring's power from the next area!
        AHAHAHAHAHA_YOU_RE_ALMOST_ON_TOP_OF_IT                                 = 8290,  -- Ahahahahaha! You're almost on top of it! It's somewhere in this area!
        THERE_IS_NOTHING_OUT_OF_THE_ORDINARY_HERE_2                            = 8291,  -- There is nothing out of the ordinary here.
        YOU_CAN_HEAR_A_STRANGE_VOICE_ITEMS_ITEMS                               = 8292,  -- You can hear a strange voice... Items, items, la la la la la`t
        OH_MY_GOB_YOU_RE_ONE_OF_THOSE                                          = 8293,  -- Oh my Gob! You're one of those adventurerurers, aren't ya? You got nothin' on me, man./lady.] I was just mindin' my own businesesess, lookin' for junk an' stuff.
        HEY_WATCH_OUT_YOU_DON_T_WANNA_FIGHT                                    = 8294,  -- Hey, watch out. You don't wanna fight me. I'll turn you into meat jerky! Wait, how about you and me be friends instead? Sound good?
        I_TRAVEL_ALL_OVER_THE_WORLD_AND_HEAR                                   = 8295,  -- I travel all over the world and hear lots of differererent stories. I even hear your stories. I can tell you one, if you want.
        NOW_LISTEN_CLOSE                                                       = 8296,  -- Now, listen close...
        OH_WELL_IF_THAT_S_THE_CASE_I                                           = 8297,  -- Oh... Well, if that's the case, I'm outta here.
        THE_GOBLIN_SLIPPED_AWAY_WHEN_YOU_WERE_NOT                              = 8298,  -- The Goblin slipped away when you were not looking...
        YOU_CAN_HEAR_A_STRANGE_RASPY_VOICE                                     = 8299,  -- You can hear a strange, raspy voice...
        I_TRAVEL_HEAR_LOTS_HEAR_STORIES_CAN_TELL                               = 8300,  -- I travel......hear lots... Hear...stories... Can tell...if...
        LISTEN                                                                 = 8301,  -- .........listen......
        OH_OUTTA_HERE                                                          = 8302,  -- Oh...... ...outta here.........
        DO_YOU_WANT_TO_HEAR_A_STORY_NO                                         = 8303,  -- Do you want to hear a story? No, thank you. Let's hear one.
        WHAT_STORY_WOULD_YOU_LIKE_TO_BE_TOLD                                   = 8304,  -- What story would you like to be told? On second thought, maybe later. The Four Musketeers(pt.1). The Four Musketeers(pt.2). A Chocobo's Tale(pt.1). A Chocobo's Tale(pt.2). Monstrosity.
        HM_WHAT_IS_THIS_HOW_DO_I_KNOW                                          = 8308,  -- Hm? What is this? %? How do I know this is not some [San d'Orian/Bastokan/Windurstian] trick?
        STEP_BACK_ADVENTURER_I_VE_GOT_MUCH_MORE                                = 8309,  -- Step back, adventurer! I've got much more important things to worry about now!
        WHAT_A_SURPRISE_ATTACK_BY_THE_BEASTMEN_AND                             = 8310,  -- What!? A surprise attack by the beastmen!? And today, of all days...
        IN_A_MATTER_OF_HOURS_A_HANDFUL_OF                                      = 8311,  -- In a matter of hours, a handful of new squires will be joining our ranks here at the outpost in [Ronfaure/Gustaberg/Sarutabaruta/Zulkheim/Norvallen/Derfland/Kolshushu/Aragoneu/Fauregandi/Valdeaunia/Qufim/Li'Telor/Kuzotz/Vollbow/the Elshimo Lowlands/the Elshimo Uplands].
        THESE_YOUNG_PATRICIANS_ARE_QUITE_SPIRITED_BUT_THEY                     = 8312,  -- These young patricians are quite spirited, but they lack valuable battle experience.
        WHILE_WE_NEED_BE_CAUTIOUS_NOT_TO_DISGRACE                              = 8313,  -- While we need be cautious not to disgrace their family names, we cannot let them fall in battle. We request your assistance in protecting the future of San d'Oria!
        IT_WILL_NOT_BE_LONG_BEFORE_A_CARAVAN                                   = 8314,  -- It will not be long before a caravan of traders in search of new trade routes arrives here at the outpost in [Ronfaure/Gustaberg/Sarutabaruta/Zulkheim/Norvallen/Derfland/Kolshushu/Aragoneu/Fauregandi/Valdeaunia/Qufim/Li'Telor/Kuzotz/Vollbow/the Elshimo Lowlands/the Elshimo Uplands].
        IF_THEY_WERE_TO_BE_INJURED_BY_THE                                      = 8315,  -- If they were to be injured by the enemy, the economy of San d'Oria could fall into chaos. We request your assistance in protecting the prosperity of our kingdom!
        A_GROUP_OF_TEMPLE_KNIGHTS_IS_EN_ROUTE                                  = 8316,  -- A group of Temple Knights is en route to this outpost here in [Ronfaure/Gustaberg/Sarutabaruta/Zulkheim/Norvallen/Derfland/Kolshushu/Aragoneu/Fauregandi/Valdeaunia/Qufim/Li'Telor/Kuzotz/Vollbow/the Elshimo Lowlands/the Elshimo Uplands] to observe our daily work.
        AH_BUT_PERHAPS_THIS_COULD_BE_A_PERFECT                                 = 8317,  -- Ah, but perhaps this could be a perfect chance to show those pampered sissies that being a true knight comprises more than just chasing about shoplifters and sweeping the chateau gardens. However, no matter how much of a grudge we may hold, we cannot let our Elvaan brothers and sisters fall in battle. Understood?
        IN_A_MATTER_OF_MOMENTS_MEMBERS_OF_THE                                  = 8318,  -- In a matter of moments, members of the Royal Guards will be arriving here in [Ronfaure/Gustaberg/Sarutabaruta/Zulkheim/Norvallen/Derfland/Kolshushu/Aragoneu/Fauregandi/Valdeaunia/Qufim/Li'Telor/Kuzotz/Vollbow/the Elshimo Lowlands/the Elshimo Uplands] to prepare us for our next campaign against the beastmen.
        IF_THE_FIENDS_ARE_CONNIVING_A_SURPRISE_ATTACK                          = 8319,  -- If the fiends are conniving a surprise attack, I expect you to do your best in assuring that no disgrace will be brought upon the guards' names, as well as preventing any unnecessary bloodshed.
        TODAY_OUR_OUTPOST_HERE_IN_IS_BLESSED_WITH                              = 8320,  -- Today, our outpost here in [Ronfaure/Gustaberg/Sarutabaruta/Zulkheim/Norvallen/Derfland/Kolshushu/Aragoneu/Fauregandi/Valdeaunia/Qufim/Li'Telor/Kuzotz/Vollbow/the Elshimo Lowlands/the Elshimo Uplands] is blessed with the honor of welcoming an ambassador from the fine Republic of Bastok.
        IF_ANYTHING_WERE_TO_HAPPEN_TO_OUR_GUEST                                = 8321,  -- If anything were to happen to our guest, it could transpire into war between our two nations. I expect you to protect the attach%i with your very life!
        IN_A_FEW_MOMENTS_A_NEW_BATCH_OF                                        = 8322,  -- In a few moments, a new batch of legionary recruits will be enlisted to the Republican Army and dispatched here to the outpost in [Ronfaure/Gustaberg/Sarutabaruta/Zulkheim/Norvallen/Derfland/Kolshushu/Aragoneu/Fauregandi/Valdeaunia/Qufim/Li'Telor/Kuzotz/Vollbow/the Elshimo Lowlands/the Elshimo Uplands].
        HOWEVER_WITHIN_THEIR_RANKS_ARE_FUTURE_SCIENTISTS_AND                   = 8323,  -- However, within their ranks are future scientists and craftsmen. Their deaths would be a great loss for the future of our nation.
        WE_MUST_ENSURE_THEIR_SAFETY_BUT_WE_ALSO                                = 8324,  -- We must ensure their safety, but we also must be careful not to prevent them from fulfilling their duties. The Republic is counting on your assistance!
        IN_A_MATTER_OF_MINUTES_A_GROUP_OF                                      = 8325,  -- In a matter of minutes, a group of mariners will be arriving at our outpost here in [Ronfaure/Gustaberg/Sarutabaruta/Zulkheim/Norvallen/Derfland/Kolshushu/Aragoneu/Fauregandi/Valdeaunia/Qufim/Li'Telor/Kuzotz/Vollbow/the Elshimo Lowlands/the Elshimo Uplands] for self-defense training.
        WE_MUST_PROVIDE_THEM_WITH_BATTLE_EXPERIENCE_BUT                        = 8326,  -- We must provide them with battle experience, but we also must ensure their safety. The Republic is counting on your assistance!
        MY_SOURCES_INDICATE_THAT_A_PARTY_OF_GOLD                               = 8327,  -- My sources indicate that a party of Gold Musketeers carrying supplies is approaching the outpost here in [Ronfaure/Gustaberg/Sarutabaruta/Zulkheim/Norvallen/Derfland/Kolshushu/Aragoneu/Fauregandi/Valdeaunia/Qufim/Li'Telor/Kuzotz/Vollbow/the Elshimo Lowlands/the Elshimo Uplands].
        THESE_SOLDIERS_ARE_THE_BEST_OF_THE_BEST                                = 8328,  -- These soldiers are the best of the best, and more than likely will not require any assistance in the event of an attack. However, if anything were to happen to them...
        LATER_TODAY_A_GROUP_OF_HIGH_RANKING_OFFICIALS                          = 8329,  -- Later today, a group of high-ranking officials from Strategic Command will be arriving here at the outpost in [Ronfaure/Gustaberg/Sarutabaruta/Zulkheim/Norvallen/Derfland/Kolshushu/Aragoneu/Fauregandi/Valdeaunia/Qufim/Li'Telor/Kuzotz/Vollbow/the Elshimo Lowlands/the Elshimo Uplands] to prepare for Bastok's next campaign against the beastmen.
        IF_ANYTHING_WERE_TO_HAPPEN_TO_THE_COMMANDERS                           = 8330,  -- If anything were to happen to the commanders, you and I would both be court-martialed! The Republic is counting on your assistance!
        I_HAVE_JUST_RECEIVED_WORD_THAT_A_GROUP                                 = 8331,  -- I have just received word that a group of ambassadors from the Federation of Windurst is en route to this outpost here in [Ronfaure/Gustaberg/Sarutabaruta/Zulkheim/Norvallen/Derfland/Kolshushu/Aragoneu/Fauregandi/Valdeaunia/Qufim/Li'Telor/Kuzotz/Vollbow/the Elshimo Lowlands/the Elshimo Uplands] to observe what measures Bastok has undertaken to maintain stability in the regions under Republican control.
        IF_THE_ATTACH_IS_WERE_TO_BE_INJURED                                    = 8332,  -- If the attach%is were to be injured on this occasion, the damage suffered to our nations' relationship would be irreparable. The Republic is counting on your assistance!
        SHORTLY_WE_WILL_BE_CONDUCTING_A_TEST_FOR                               = 8333,  -- Shortly, we will be conducting a test for our mercenary candidates here at the outpost in [Ronfaure/Gustaberg/Sarutabaruta/Zulkheim/Norvallen/Derfland/Kolshushu/Aragoneu/Fauregandi/Valdeaunia/Qufim/Li'Telor/Kuzotz/Vollbow/the Elshimo Lowlands/the Elshimo Uplands].
        THIS_EXAM_IS_TO_HELP_US_JUDGE_THE                                      = 8334,  -- This exam is to help us judge the candidates' skill in battle and help us separate those with talent from those who are bound for deskwork.
        BUT_AFTER_AN_ATTACK_BY_THE_BEASTMEN_THERE                              = 8335,  -- But after an attack by the beastmen...there won't be any candidates left to grade! You've got to help us give these kids a fighting chance!
        IT_WON_T_BE_LONG_BEFORE_A_PARTY                                        = 8336,  -- It won't be long before a party of Federation scholars will be arriving here at the outpost in [Ronfaure/Gustaberg/Sarutabaruta/Zulkheim/Norvallen/Derfland/Kolshushu/Aragoneu/Fauregandi/Valdeaunia/Qufim/Li'Telor/Kuzotz/Vollbow/the Elshimo Lowlands/the Elshimo Uplands] to do research on the local wildlife.
        THESE_SCIENTISTS_ARE_MORE_POWERFUL_WITH_THEIR_PENS                     = 8337,  -- These scientists are more powerful with their pens than their swords...but that won't help them against a beastman attack! You've got to help us protect them!
        HMMM_LATER_TODAY_A_SMALL_GROUP_OF_WIZE                                 = 8338,  -- Hmmm... Later today, a small group of Wize Wizards will be arriving to observe our daily work here at the outpost in [Ronfaure/Gustaberg/Sarutabaruta/Zulkheim/Norvallen/Derfland/Kolshushu/Aragoneu/Fauregandi/Valdeaunia/Qufim/Li'Telor/Kuzotz/Vollbow/the Elshimo Lowlands/the Elshimo Uplands].
        I_SAY_THAT_WE_GIVE_THEM_SOMETHING_TO                                   = 8339,  -- I say that we give them something to remember! %! It's up to you to prove to those bigwigs that we are the ones who maintain the peace in the Federation! Give those beastmen all you've got! (Just don't let the Wize Wizards get hurt...)
        TODAY_A_PARTY_OF_FEDERATION_PATRIARCHS_IS_SCHEDULED                    = 8340,  -- Today, a party of Federation Patriarchs is scheduled to arrive at the outpost here in [Ronfaure/Gustaberg/Sarutabaruta/Zulkheim/Norvallen/Derfland/Kolshushu/Aragoneu/Fauregandi/Valdeaunia/Qufim/Li'Telor/Kuzotz/Vollbow/the Elshimo Lowlands/the Elshimo Uplands] to plan for Windurst's next campaign against the beastmen.
        IF_ANYTHING_WERE_TO_HAPPEN_TO_THEM_WE                                  = 8341,  -- If anything were to happen to them, we'd all be reassigned to latrine duty! If you know what's good for you, you won't let anyone lay a finger on them!
        OH_WHY_DID_THE_MILITARY_ATTACH_IS_FROM                                 = 8342,  -- Oh, why did the military attach%is from San d'Oria have to come to our outpost in [Ronfaure/Gustaberg/Sarutabaruta/Zulkheim/Norvallen/Derfland/Kolshushu/Aragoneu/Fauregandi/Valdeaunia/Qufim/Li'Telor/Kuzotz/Vollbow/the Elshimo Lowlands/the Elshimo Uplands] now?
        I_SHUDDER_TO_THINK_WHAT_WOULD_HAPPEN_IF                                = 8343,  -- I shudder to think what would happen if an ambassador was injured...or worse! Get out there and protect those Elvaan with your life!
        EXCELLENT_WORK_YOUR_EFFORTS_HELPED_PROTECT_THE_FUTURE                  = 8344,  -- Excellent work! Your efforts helped protect the future of our nation. Divide this among your companions.
        OUR_NATION_SUFFERED_AN_ENORMOUS_LOSS_TODAY_WE                          = 8345,  -- Our nation suffered an enormous loss today. We must begin reinforcing our defenses immediately!
        YOUR_INABILITY_TO_COMPLETE_THE_MISSION_HAS_LED                         = 8346,  -- Your inability to complete the mission has led to our defeat. The last thing our nation needs is an incompetent adventurer!
        YOU_FOUGHT_HARD_AND_YOU_PROVED_YOURSELF_WORTHY                         = 8347,  -- You fought hard, and you proved yourself worthy. You are a great asset to the nation.
        WE_COMMEND_YOU_ON_YOUR_SERVICES_IN_HELPING                             = 8348,  -- We commend you on your services in helping us avert the beastmen's attack. I do not see them attacking us again any time soon.
        THIS_AREA_IS_CURRENTLY_CONDUCTING_A_BALLISTA_MATCH                     = 8349,  -- This area is currently conducting a Ballista match. I have no time to trouble myself with your beastman trinkets.
        A_PARTY_MEMBER_HAS_AN_NPC_CALLED_UP_2                                  = 8350,  -- A party member has an NPC called up. You cannot take part in this event.
        I_WAS_THINKING_THIS_OUT_LOUD_WHEN_AN                                   = 8351,  -- I was thinking this out loud when an Elvaan girl passing by stopped to talk to me.
        BUT_WHAT_ABOUT_MOOGLES_THEY_VE_GOT_WINGS                               = 8352,  -- But what about moogles? They've got wings, and they can fly, but you wouldn't call 'em birds. They've got those funny antennae, too, but they're not insects, either.
        WHEN_I_RESPONDED_TO_HER_REMARK_WITH_THE                                = 8353,  -- When I responded to her remark with the fact that both moogles and chocobos are animals, this is what she asked:
        THEN_WHAT_S_THE_DIFFERENCE_BETWEEN_ANIMALS_AND                         = 8354,  -- Then what's the difference between animals and people?
        I_ANSWERED_PEOPLE_ARE_SMARTER_THAN_ANIMALS_AND                         = 8355,  -- I answered, People are smarter than animals. And then she retorted, People sure are more sly!
        AHAHAHA_DON_T_GET_ALL_HUFFY_ON_ME                                      = 8356,  -- Ahahaha, don't get all huffy on me! I stopped to talk because what you were saying was important.
        PEOPLE_ARE_ALL_DIFFERENT_FROM_ONE_ANOTHER_THEY                         = 8357,  -- People are all different from one another. They're different from animals, and different from plants. This difference is what makes it all worth it.
        THERE_ARE_LOTS_OF_WAYS_TO_THINK_AND                                    = 8358,  -- There are lots of ways to think and feel, and things to know and to believe. But in the end, we all come from the same source.
        THAT_S_TRUE_FOR_BOTH_PEOPLE_AND_ANIMALS                                = 8359,  -- That's true for both people and animals.
        WE_ALL_HAVE_THIS_THING_CALLED_A_SOUL                                   = 8360,  -- We all have this thing called a soul. The souls of animals are pure and simple.
        LOOK_OVER_THERE_THAT_CHOCOBO_IS_LIVING_PROOF                           = 8361,  -- Look over there. That chocobo is living proof.
        YOU_SHOULD_ASK_SOMEONE_HOW_THAT_CHOCOBO_WAS                            = 8362,  -- You should ask someone how that chocobo was born. Then you'll have your answers.
        AND_THEN_SHE_WENT_ON_HER_WAY                                           = 8363,  -- ...And then she went on her way.
        I_WENT_TO_FIND_OUT_HOW_THAT_CHOCOBO                                    = 8364,  -- I went to find out how that chocobo was born, but no one could tell me.
        SHALOTT_SAID_THE_CHOCOBO_S_MOTHER_WAS_FROM                             = 8365,  -- Shalott said the chocobo's mother was from the stables in Bastok.
        SHE_SAID_IT_WAS_A_SPECIAL_CHOCOBO_THAT                                 = 8366,  -- She said it was a special chocobo that had silver-colored feathers on its neck.
        HOW_I_WISH_I_COULD_GO_TO_BASTOK                                        = 8367,  -- How I wish I could go to Bastok to see her for myself.
        I_WONDER_IF_THAT_ELVAAN_GIRL_WILL_BE                                   = 8368,  -- I wonder if that Elvaan girl will be passing by again anytime soon...
        THAT_ELVAAN_GIRL_TOLD_ME_THAT_BOTH_PEOPLE                              = 8369,  -- That Elvaan girl told me that both people and animals have souls. She said that the souls of animals are far more pure than those of people.
        SHE_ALSO_TOLD_ME_I_WOULD_UNDERSTAND_WHAT                               = 8370,  -- She also told me I would understand what she meant if I found out how that chocobo was born.
        ACCORDING_TO_SHALOTT_THE_CHOCOBO_S_MOTHER_IS                           = 8371,  -- According to Shalott, the chocobo's mother is from the stables in Bastok. How I wish I could go there to see her for myself...
        WHAT_CAN_I_DO_FOR_YOU_IF_YOU                                           = 8372,  -- What can I do for you? If you want to ride a chocobo, one of the girls over there can help you out.
        LATELY_A_LOT_OF_ADVENTURERS_SEEM_TO_BE                                 = 8373,  -- Lately, a lot of adventurers seem to be forgetting that a chocobo is an animal, not an object.
        YOU_SHOULD_KEEP_THAT_IN_MIND_AS_YOU                                    = 8374,  -- You should keep that in mind as you're enjoying that easy ride through monster-ridden badlands. Have a safe journey.
        A_CHOCOBO_WITH_SILVER_COLORED_FEATHERS                                 = 8375,  -- A chocobo with silver-colored feathers...?
        AH_YOU_D_BE_TALKING_ABOUT_SILVER_COMET                                 = 8376,  -- Ah, you'd be talking about Silver Comet.
        SHE_USED_TO_BE_THE_MOUNT_OF_A                                          = 8377,  -- She used to be the mount of a highly ranked general in the Bastokan navy.
        THE_GENERAL_S_SON_RECEIVED_THE_CHOCOBO_AS                              = 8378,  -- The general's son received the chocobo as a coming-of-age present, which he promptly took advantage of to leave Bastok.
        FOR_THE_LONGEST_TIME_NO_ONE_SAW_HIDE                                   = 8379,  -- For the longest time, no one saw hide nor hair of man or beast--until eventually, Silver Comet came wandering back into town...alone.
